<h1>@PKG_NAME@</h1>
<p align=right><a href="@TAR_FILE@">@TAR_FILE@</a> (@DATE@)</p>

<p>
This package provides an interface to Amazon's Simple DB API.
It allows one to
<ul>
  <li> create new domains
  <li> delete domains
  <li> list domains
  <li> get information about a domain

  <li> add data items to a domain
  <li> retrieve the value of items from a domain
  <li> delete items from a domain

  <li> perform <b>SELECT</b> queries on a domain
      
</ul>

At present, the interface is a relatively low-level mapping from the
REST operations to R functions.  The <b>select()</b> function provides
slightly higher-level functionality in that it turns the results in an
R data frame.  Similarly, <b>putAttributes()</b> uploads R vector or
list objects.
But there is a significant opportunity to add  higher-level
functionality and

<ul>
  <li> treat the remote tables as R data frames
  <li> work with values other than strings
</ul>

</p>
<p>
This package is related in some senses to the
<a href="../RAmazonS3">RAmazonS3</a> package.
</p>


